5.32 pm local time Ishant's done a splendid job, scoring 23 out of the last-wicket stand of 31. Tendulkar walks off the field to loud cheers once again, he remains undefeated on 154. Could he have shielded the tail better? Well the last three wickets added 187 runs so you have to give him credit. India lead by 69 runs in the first-innings. Australia have about 30 minutes to negotiate before stumps. Matthew Hayden and Phil Jaques will run out in less than ten minutes.

If you're not going to be at your computer for the final 30 minutes of play, you can still get Cricinfo's commentary on your mobile phone by clicking here.
